A vintage 1970s-style rotary telephone melting and transforming into a cascade of green digital code streams and circuit board patterns, sitting on a wooden desk in a warmly lit home office. The phone's spiral cord dissolves into ethernet cables that snake across the desk surface. Through a window behind the desk, a soft golden sunrise illuminates the scene. The image has the warm, slightly faded color palette of old Kodachrome film photography, with subtle grain and vignetting at the edges. A small penguin figurine sits beside the transforming phone, observing the metamorphosis with curiosity.
